name: Sundel Bolong
description: Sundel bolong (in Malay: sundal bolong) is a mythical ghost from the archipelago which is generally described as a beautiful woman with long hair and a long white dress with a hole ("penetrating hole") on the back which is slightly covered by long hair so that the internal organs of the body are covered with hair. The stomach is visible.[1] Many think that Sundel Bolong is the same as Kuntilanak, because in the myth, both of them are depicted with long hair and wearing a white dress. ).[1] The myth of the sundel bolong ghost has also become a common myth in Malaysia after being brought by immigrants from the archipelago.[1] Wikipedia
